    "en_q": "A SysOps administrator has an AWS CloudFormation template that is used to deploy an encrypted Amazon Machine Image (AMI). The CloudFormation template will be used in a second account so the SysOps administrator copies the encrypted AMI to the second account. When launching the new CloudFormation stack in the second account, it fails. Which action should the SysOps administrator take to correct the issue?",
